* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|en|/ˈdɪfɚ/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-differ.ogg|Audio (GA)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɪfə(r)}}
* {{hyphenation|en|dif|fer}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} Not to have the same [[trait]]s or [[characteristic]]s; to be [[unalike]] or [[distinct]].
#: {{synonyms|en|Thesaurus:differ}}
#: {{ux|en|These shoes only '''differ''' from those ones in having slightly longer laces.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|people, groups, etc.}} To have [[diverge|diverging]] [[opinion]]s, [[disagree]].
#* Canning
#*: If the honourable gentleman '''differs''' with me on that subject, I differ as heartily with him, and shall always rejoice to differ.

